{{Infobox Website | name = Index Fungorum | logo = | url = [http://www.indexfungorum.org/ IndexFungorum.org] | alexa = | commercial = No | type = [[Database]] | registration = Not required | owner = Index Fungorum Partnership | author = Index Fungorum Partnership | launch date = | current status = }} {{DISPLAYTITLE:''Index Fungorum''}} '''''Index Fungorum''''' is an international project to index all formal names ([[Binomial nomenclature|scientific name]]s) in the [[Fungus]] [[Kingdom (biology)|Kingdom]]. {{as of|2015}} the project is based at the [[Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew]], one of three partners along with [[Landcare Research New Zealand Limited|Landcare Research]] and the Institute of Microbiology, [[Chinese Academy of Sciences]].
It is somewhat comparable to the [[International Plant Names Index]] (IPNI), in which the Royal Botanic Gardens is also involved. A difference is that where IPNI does not indicate [[Correct name (botany)|correct name]]s, the ''Index Fungorum'' does indicate the status of a name. In the returns from the search page a currently correct name is indicated in green, while others are in blue (a few, aberrant usages of names are indicated in red). All names are linked to pages giving the correct name, with lists of [[Synonym (taxonomy)|synonym]]s.
Index Fungorum is one of three nomenclatural repositories recognized by the [[Nomenclature Committee for Fungi]]; the others are ''[[MycoBank]]'' and ''[[Fungal Names]]''.<ref name="Redhead 2013"/>
==Current names in ''Index Fungorum'' (''Species Fungorum'')== The main part of ''Index Fungorum'' is intended to be a global list of all fungus names which have ever been validly defined, but many of them are conflicting or no longer used. ''Species Fungorum'' is a closely related project based at the [[w:Royal Botanical Gardens, Kew|Royal Botanical Gardens, Kew]] supported by [[w:CABI (organisation)|CABI]] to decide a consistent subset of the ''Index Fungorum'' names which can be recommended as currently valid. It is possible to search in either the ''Index Fungorum'' or the ''Species Fungorum'' list separately and the ''Index Fungorum'' results also give a cross-reference to ''Species Fungorum'' where an entry is available - names without such a reference are generally only of historical interest and should not be considered reliable for present use.<ref name=IF>See the pop-up "Help with searching" at {{cite web |url=http://www.indexfungorum.org/Names/Names.asp |title=''Index Fungorum'' home page|work=Index Fungorum|publisher=Royal Botanic Gardens Kew |accessdate=2016-10-25}}.</ref><ref name=SF>{{cite web |url=http://www.speciesfungorum.org/ |title=''Species Fungorum'' home page|work=Species Fungorum |publisher=Royal Botanic Gardens Kew |accessdate=2016-10-25}}</ref>
==Life Science Identifiers (LSIDs)== ''Index Fungorum'' provides [[LSID|Life Science Identifiers (LSIDs)]] for records in its database.
==Services== ''Index Fungorum'' provides a [[SOAP]] protocol [[web service]] for searching its database and retrieving records. A [[Web Services Description Language|WSDL]] file describing the services is available.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indexfungorum.org/IXFWebService/Fungus.asmx|title=Fungus Web Service|website=www.indexfungorum.org}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Australian Plant Name Index]] *[[Index Kewensis]] *[[International Plant Names Index]]
